events.name: GDG St. Albert Meetup/ I/O 2019 Tech Discussion /  G-suite experience
events.description:
This will be our first local GDG St. Albert meeting following the I/O 2019 conference held in Sunnyvale California.

As GDG St. Albert organizer, I look forward to discussing some of the exciting announcements from the 2019 Google I/O conference.

After a short introduction and get to know each other session, I propose we watch the latest keynote talk from I/O 19. The keynote generally hits all of the highlights from all of the announcements.

I also suggest that we discuss / try some of the new collaboration tools that were announced recently.

Next venue: Wednesday May 29 in St. Albert, Alberta.
Bridge 297 - Lower Deck Suite
enter by the back gate or front door at 97 Lombard Cres.
Back gate entry doors open at 17:30

events.name: GDG St. Albert Chapter "Winter Fun" - Sledding at Langholm Park
events.description:
This meetup is intended to provide an opportunity for chapter members to get to know each other in a casual environment. Participation is optional, gravity does the rest. I have a couple innexpensive toboggans for anyone that wants to try sledding. If you have your own sled, bring it along. Dress warm, make sure you snow garmets. Lets find a little winter fun on the snow.

At approximately 4pm some hot co-co, coffee and pizza will be available on a first come first serve basis at the back gate at 97.

I hope our new GDG meeting room is ready and we can discuss building a team of organizers and experts in our community to ensure our St. Albert Chapter continues to provide value to residents.

If time permits, we will review video of recent Keynote speaches from the Chrome Enterprise developers summit's.

Next meeting TBD
events.how_to_find_us: Park on Langholm Drive in the vicinity of the Langholm Park sign. The GDG St Albert Flag is attached to the Back Gate at 97.
